<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-0809 </DOCNO><TEXT>The desire to avoid a nuclear war, and to curb the arms race on mutuallyacceptable terms, is a basic motivation of Soviet policy. The obstaclesto agreement lie not in the mindless aggressiveness of either party,but in an asymmetry of interests and outlooks that leads to grave mutualmisperceptions and constitutes a fundamental obstacle to rational negotiationand compromise. The task of this paper is to explore the domestic andinternational factors affecting Soviet defense policy before discussingthe Soviet approach to arms control more specifically.</TEXT></DOC>